A dramatic satellite view of Earth from space in Studio Ghibli animation style, showing the Pacific Ocean with a massive spiraling hurricane system dominating the frame, its white cloud bands swirling with ethereal beauty against the deep blue ocean. The curve of Earth is visible at the edge, with soft gradients of atmosphere creating a dreamy glow. The storm's eye is clearly defined, surrounded by painterly brushstroke-like cloud formations in whites and grays. Sunlight catches the edges of the clouds, giving them a luminous golden rim. Small island chains are barely visible beneath wispy cloud cover. The overall mood is both ominous and breathtakingly beautiful, capturing nature's raw power through the gentle, hand-painted aesthetic characteristic of Japanese animation, with soft color transitions and a sense of quiet awe at the scale of natural forces.
